The Muger sub-basin is located to the southeast of the Abay Basin. Studies (
 Azagegn et al., 2015; 
 Berehanu et al., 2017) show that the aquifer system is connected to the upper Awash basin, which drains towards the southeast. This singularity combined with a lack of data makes calibration of the Muger basin very difficult. On average, the mean contribution of the Muger sub-basin is 0.97%.
